02/09/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Twenty-two members of a notorious Balkan criminal gang were arrested on Tuesday (September 1st) in a joint operation by Serbian and Bosnian police. Eight members, including the alleged leader of the group -- Bosnian Darko Elez -- were detained in Serbia, while the remaining 14 were arrested in Bosnia and Herzegovina. Some of those arrested are police officers themselves. They are suspected of murder, blackmail, robbery, drugs and weapons smuggling, and money laundering. Additional arrests are expected. (Beta, Tanjug, B92, RTRS, BHRT - 01/09/09)
